Did you know that Raphael Mazzucco travelled Brazil for 27 days, taking in the country's beauty and gaining inspiration for the latest instalment of his renowned collection: 'Grass Roots'? ⁠
⁠
The favoured photographer, who travelled around the globe shooting campaigns with iconic brands, creates an authentic and raw visual palette by taking his experience, passion for the abstract, and little pieces from where he has ventured, including bright pigments and journal entries, then immortalised his memories by layering them into his art. ⁠
⁠
Before the official launch of limited edition artworks from the collection on the 29th June, we're giving you the chance to pre-order your favourite piece from Raphael's beautiful range of bold original new works. To find out more, click the link in bio.

New "Grass Roots" Collection

Today is the day! Raphael Mazzucco's latest edition of his 'Grass Roots' collection is now available in our galleries and online!⁠
⁠
The colour palette has developed from the raw beauty of Africa in sepia tones from his previous instalment to the breakthrough of rich hues of oranges, reds, blues, and yellows, representing the vibrant Brazilian culture. The vivid pigments break through these pieces as @raphaelmazzucco injects aspects of his escapades into his brand-new artworks. Through his artworks, he celebrates the Amazonian culture while transporting his viewers onto his travels with him and allowing us to bring the beauty of nature to our walls. ⁠
⁠
To browse this stunning release, click the link in our bio.

Raphael Mazzucco: the Canadian visionary behind the lens

Mazzucco’s unique approach to photography sets him apart from the crowd. He believes that his photography is more controlled, while the artistic elements, such as painting and layering, allow him to embrace a sense of freedom and unpredictability. “I feel like I’m organized on the inside and unorganized on the outside,” he muses.
